\begin_layout Standard
Finally, Angrist makes a case for the use of direct energy conversion.
 He goes through the increasing energy needs, highlighting the fact that
 we will not be able to meet our energy needs for 2000 at our current price
 per kilowatt hour.
 He then describes the benefits of direct energy conversion for terrestrial
 and space applications.
 One of his more esoteric arguments is that 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

when a process can occur directly rather than by passing through several
 intermediate steps, it seems reasonable to assume that it may take place
 more efficiently.
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


