 Particularly, he points out the localization of energy needs makes small,
 modular type generation more elegant as a solution.
 He also comes back to the overarching concepts: that direct energy conversion
 usually generates energy from energy income to the earth, a more sustainable
 solution, or that it converts waste heat or products from other energy
 sources, thus augmenting the existing energy economy.
